Workflow Governance
Policy Template
A practical governance template that keeps AI-assisted workflows safe, consistent, and enforceable.

Document Type: Policy Template
Title: Workflow Governance
Author: AI Virtual Agency
Contact: biztechwellnessai@gmail.com
Website: www.aivirtualagency.com

Policy 1 — Purpose
This policy defines how AI is allowed to support workflows inside a small owner-led service business without creating risk, confusion, or drift.

Policy 2 — Principles
- No automation without structure
- Humans own decisions, AI supports clarity
- AI may draft, classify, summarize, and propose rules
- AI may not execute irreversible actions without review

Policy 3 — Risk tiers
Tier 1 (Low Risk): Summaries, drafts, formatting, Internal notes, SOP drafting.
Tier 2 (Medium Risk): Decision routing suggestions, Boundary rule suggestions, Client email drafts.
Tier 3 (High Risk): Legal language, Pricing changes, Contract terms, Anything customer-facing without review.

Policy 4 — Decision routing standard
All inbound “decision noise” is classified:
- Green: team acts under a boundary
- Yellow: team acts + notifies
- Red: escalates with required context

Policy 5 — Required human review
AI-generated outputs must be reviewed when: Customer-facing communication, Financial commitments, Legal commitments, Reputation-impact decisions.

Policy 6 — Workflow ownership
Each workflow must have: Owner, Boundaries, Escalation conditions, Update cadence.

Policy 7 — Drift control
If a rule is repeatedly overridden, it must be revised. Do not allow exceptions to become the new operating model silently.

Policy 8 — Templates (copy/paste)
Workflow Record: Workflow name, Owner, What AI supports, Boundaries, Escalation conditions, Approved examples, Forbidden examples.
Monthly Review Checklist: What escalations repeated? Which boundaries worked? Which rules were overridden? What needs tightening?
